.TH simple_shell 1 "August 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [command_file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple command-line interpreter that mimics the behavior of
.BR /bin/sh .
It reads commands from the standard input and executes them, or from a file in non-interactive mode.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
- Displays a prompt and waits for commands in interactive mode.
.TP
- Executes commands with arguments.
.TP
- Uses the PATH variable to find executables.
.TP
- Handles built-in commands:
  .RS
  .B exit
  Exit the shell.
  .br
  .B env
  Print the current environment.
  .RE
.TP
- Works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.TP
- Handles EOF (Ctrl+D) correctly.
.TP
- Prints errors in the format:
  .I argv[0]: line_number: command: not found

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
file1 file2 file3
($) exit
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2 file3
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1)

